  "summary": "<a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/03/19/all-five-dna-rna-building-blocks-found-in-asteroid-ryugu-samples.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"All five DNA/RNA building blocks found in asteroid Ryugu samples\"><img alt=\"Representational image (Boing Boing/Midjourney)\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/asteroid-1.jpg?fit=1200%2C800&amp;quality=60&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"1200\" /></a><p>Every nucleobase needed to build DNA and RNA — adenine, guanine, cytosine, thymine, and uracil — has been found in rock samples from the asteroid Ryugu, <a href=\"https://phys.org/news/2026-03-ryugu-asteroid-samples-dna-rna.html\">according to a study published in <em>Nature Astronomy</em></a>. Previous research in 2023 had found only uracil. &#8212; <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/03/19/all-five-dna-rna-building-blocks-found-in-asteroid-ryugu-samples.htm",
